  "page": {
    "documentTitle": "布里丹之驢 | Concept Reading Lab",
    "bodyClass": "knowledge-page knowledge-buridans-ass",
    "heroHtml": "<div class=\"hero-inner\">\n  <div>\n    <p class=\"kicker\">Knowledge Study / choice / paralysis / tie-break</p>\n    <h1>布里丹之驢</h1>\n    <p class=\"topic-subtitle\">Buridan&#x27;s Ass</p>\n    <p class=\"thesis\">當兩個選項看起來幾乎一樣好、理由又彼此抵銷時，問題不一定是資訊太少，有時反而是缺少一個能打破平手的決策規則。</p>\n    <div class=\"hero-prompt\">\n      <strong>Read For</strong>\n      <p>這一頁要把『兩個都很好』和『因此什麼都做不了』拆開，因為很多決策卡住不是缺資料，而是沒有平手時該怎麼決定的規則。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <aside class=\"hero-note\" aria-label=\"主題資訊\">\n    <dl class=\"lexical-meta lexical-meta--knowledge\" aria-label=\"主題摘要\">\n      <div>\n        <dt>主題類型</dt>\n        <dd>悖論 / 選擇癱瘓</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>核心問題</dt>\n        <dd>Perfectly balanced options can produce paralysis</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>主要判準</dt>\n        <dd>選項對稱、差異可感度、決策規則、機會成本</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>讀完產出</dt>\n        <dd>能在近似等價選項前建立打破僵局的實用判準</dd>\n      </div>\n    </dl>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-map\" aria-label=\"閱讀結構示意\">\n      <span>平手</span>\n      <span>卡住</span>\n      <span>規則</span>\n    </div>\n  </aside>\n</div>",
    "mainHtml": "<aside class=\"compass\" aria-label=\"頁內導覽\">\n  <span>Reading Path</span>\n  <a href=\"#core\">讀法總覽</a>\n  <a href=\"#setup\">問題設定</a>\n  <a href=\"#lenses\">判準透鏡</a>\n  <a href=\"#psychology\">心理連結</a>\n  <a href=\"#applications\">現實映射</a>\n  <a href=\"#misreadings\">誤讀校正</a>\n  <a href=\"#questions\">延伸提問</a>\n  <a href=\"#sources\">來源</a>\n</aside>\n\n<article class=\"article\">\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"core\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Orientation</p>\n      <h2>當理由完全打平時，真正缺的常不是更多分析，而是容許決定的規則</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">布里丹之驢這則思想故事之所以耐讀，是因為它把理性選擇的極限縮成一個尷尬畫面：兩邊都合理，於是動不了。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"core-card\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Core Tension</p>\n      <p>追求最合理很重要，但若你要求每次都要有明顯優勢才行動，在高相近選項下，等待本身就會變成代價。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"principle-strip\" aria-label=\"本頁讀法\">\n      <div>\n        <span>01</span>\n        <strong>先承認平手本來就會發生</strong>\n        <p>不是每個選擇都存在顯著優勝者。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>02</span>\n        <strong>再設計 tie-break</strong>\n        <p>當差異小到不足以決定時，要靠次級準則或隨機化讓決策前進。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>03</span>\n        <strong>最後把不決定也列入成本</strong>\n        <p>繼續卡住不是零成本，它同樣會消耗時間與機會。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"setup\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Setup</p>\n      <h2>從兩個都不差、卻因此一直選不下去的局面開始</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">布里丹之驢不是在笑理性，而是在提醒理性也需要能處理平手的規則。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"definition-grid\">\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>最小劇情</strong>\n        <p>兩個技術方案在成本、風險與效能上幾乎打平，團隊於是開一輪又一輪會，卻遲遲不敢拍板。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>真正難點</strong>\n        <p>你越想找決定性證據，越可能忽略其實平手本身就是一種正常狀態。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"concept-flow\" aria-label=\"問題展開\">\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">選項高度接近</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">主要判準無法分勝負</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">沒有 tie-break 便陷入停滯</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"paradox-frame\">\n      <strong>Key Point</strong>\n      <p>布里丹之驢的實用價值，在於提醒你：成熟的決策系統要能優雅處理平手。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"lenses\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Lenses</p>\n      <h2>四個看平手僵局的角度</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">真正要問的不是哪邊完美勝出，而是哪套規則能在不完美中讓你往前。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"lens-grid\">\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>差異大小</strong>\n        <p>選項差距是否已小到再分析也未必帶來實質價值？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>次級準則</strong>\n        <p>是否能用可逆性、學習價值或切換成本作為第二層判準？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>決策時限</strong>\n        <p>拖延本身正在吞掉多少機會與注意力？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>可回頭性</strong>\n        <p>若選錯也容易調整，平手時就更值得先動。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"table-wrap\">\n      <table>\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            <th>情境</th>\n            <th>卡住的原因</th>\n            <th>可用的打平方法</th>\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td>工具選型</td>\n            <td>主要指標都差不多</td>\n            <td>優先選切換成本較低或學習價值較高者</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>職涯選擇</td>\n            <td>兩邊都可接受</td>\n            <td>看哪邊更可逆或更能提供資訊增量</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>產品方向</td>\n            <td>資料無法明顯分勝負</td>\n            <td>先做小型試點而不是全押等待</td>\n          </tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"psychology\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Psychology</p>\n      <h2>為什麼平手這麼容易把人困住</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">因為我們常把『還沒找到最好』誤當成『還不該決定』。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>錯誤恐懼會放大平手</strong>\n        <p>當差異小卻後果感覺重大時，人更難接受任一選擇。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>更多分析像在買安心</strong>\n        <p>即使新增資訊價值很低，持續分析仍讓人感覺自己還在努力。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>不決定被誤讀成中立</strong>\n        <p>其實停滯本身也是一種有成本的決策。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"micro-note\">布里丹之驢不是叫你隨便選，而是叫你在平手時準備好規則，不要把自己餓死在比較表前。</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"applications\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Applications</p>\n      <h2>把打平規則帶回技術與策略決策</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">對工程與產品團隊來說，最浪費的不一定是選錯，而是很多低差異選項被拖成高成本停滯。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>技術評估</strong>\n        <p>若兩套方案都可用，先看哪個更容易 rollback 或更容易在實作中獲得新資訊。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>需求排序</strong>\n        <p>接近等價時，可用時機性或依賴解鎖價值打平。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>個人工具</strong>\n        <p>若兩個工具都夠好，與其再花兩週比較，不如先定一個試用期限。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <ul class=\"bullet-list\">\n      <li>重要決策流程最好預先定義：當主要判準打平時，我們用什麼次級規則前進。</li>\n      <li>若一個選項高度可逆，平手時通常比你以為的更值得先做而不是先等。</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"misreadings\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Misreadings</p>\n      <h2>三個常見誤讀</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">布里丹之驢不是反分析，而是反對把分析當成無限期延後決策的藉口。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"collocation-list\" aria-label=\"常見誤讀\">\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>平手就隨便選</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>不是。先用合理的次級準則縮短僵局。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>這只在哲學故事裡有</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>技術選型、職涯與產品優先順序都很常見。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只要資料再多一點就能解</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>有時差異本來就小，多資料也不會帶來決定性訊號。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"questions\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Questions</p>\n      <h2>我是真的還缺關鍵資訊，還是只是沒有平手時的規則</h2>\n      </div>\n    <div class=\"prompt-grid\">\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>再分析一週，會真的改變決策，還是只是延後決策</strong>\n        <p>這能幫你測新增資訊價值。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>如果今天一定得選，我會用哪個次級準則打平</strong>\n        <p>那個準則通常本來就該被提早說出來。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"template-note\">\n      <strong>延伸路線</strong>\n      <p>延伸閱讀可接 decision theory、tie-breaking 與 bounded rationality。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"sources\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Sources</p>\n      <h2>來源與整理方式</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這一頁以 Buridan&#x27;s Ass 的思想情境為主，再把問題帶回平手決策與組織僵局。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"source-grid\">\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>主概念</strong>\n        <p>Buridan&#x27;s ass 條目整理了這則思想實驗如何呈現對稱選擇下的停滯問題。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buridan%27s_ass\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Buridan&#x27;s Ass</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>理論背景</strong>\n        <p>Decision theory 可作為對照，理解理性選擇何時需要額外規則處理平手。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decision_theory\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Decision Theory</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>近鄰概念</strong>\n        <p>Bounded rationality 有助於理解現實決策為何需要足夠好與實用規則。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bounded_rationality\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Bounded Rationality</a>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"reference-box\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"section-label\">Reference</p>\n        <h2>下一步</h2>\n        <p>讀完後可以挑一個你卡很久的二選一題目，先定一條打平規則，再看是否能立即往前。</p>\n      </div>\n      <a class=\"reference-link\" href=\"../knowledge-topic-template.html\">打開模板</a>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</article>"
  }
}
